            </owl:Restriction>
        </rdfs:subClassOf>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">cubic equivalency assertion</rdfs:label>
        <skos:definition xml:lang="en">cubic equivalency assertion is a symmetry equivalency assertion which is used to infer crystallographic equivalence between single crystallographic direction /plane and family of directions/planes under the cubic crystal symmetry.
In particular, it considers &lt;100&gt;, &lt;110&gt;, and &lt;111&gt; families of crystallographic directions, as well as {100}, {110}, {111} families of crystallographic planes</skos:definition>
    </owl:Class>
    


